{"questionId":"3595","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Nitric oxide reacts with chlorine.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">2NO (g) + Cl<sub>2</sub> (g) → 2NOCl (g)</p>\n<p>The following experimental data were obtained at 101.3 kPa and 263 K.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/19e00f1edefd9a759d8ba9fccd0cbc8a9172789b.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Deduce the order of reaction with respect to Cl<sub>2</sub> and NO.</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/dc5bf52b23702c3f6b8c0da86595ea67ed4623d2.png\"></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em>Cl<sub>2</sub>:</em> first<br><em>NO:</em> second</p>","meta":{"questionId":"3595","referenceCode":"17N.2.hl.TZ0.2e.i","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Deduce the order of reaction with respect to Cl2 and NO.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"e.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 16: Chemical kinetics","16.1 Rate expression and reaction mechanism","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 16: Chemical kinetics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}